Date: Fri, 9 May 1997
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: OIE Disease Status Vol. 10 - No. 19
OIE Follow-up report No. 2
Translation of a fax received on 9 May 1997 from Dr J. Nombela Maqueda,
Deputy Director General of Animal Health, Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries
and Food, Madrid:
End of previous report period: 24 April 1997(see Disease=
Information,10[18],65)
End of this report period: 7 May 1997.
New outbreaks:
Location No. of outbreaks
Bell Lloch d'Urgel district, L=E9rida province,=20
Catalonia Autonomous Community 2
Linyola district, L=E9rida province,=20
Catalonia Autonomous Community 2
Montgai district, L=E9rida province,
Catalonia Autonomous Community 3
Torregrosa district, L=E9rida province,
Catalonia Autonomous Community 1
Total number of outbreaks identified since 1 January 1997: eighteen (18).
Total number of animals in the new outbreaks:
susceptible cases deaths destroyed slaughtered
3,275 * 1,260 109 3,166 0
* 2,637 fattening pigs, 398 breeding pigs and 240 piglets.
Diagnosis:
A: Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Animal Production and Health
Laboratory, Algete (Madrid)
B: Diagnostic tests used:direct immunofluorescence and ELISA

Epidemiology:
A: Source of agent / origin of infection: these are secondary outbreaks
B: Mode of spread: investigations are under way
Control measures during reporting period: stamping out; ban on movement in
the vicinity of the affected farms; protection and surveillance zones;
epidemiological investigations under way.
